  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop the <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1614618682814-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1614618682814-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1614618682814-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1614618682814-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1614618682814-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 15-17 min or until fork-tender, then drain and return to the pot (you want them to be crumbly!)</p><p>Once done, drain and set aside, reserve the pot for later</p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1614618688262-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1614618688262-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1614618688262-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1614618688262-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1614618688262-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken breasts</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until golden</p><p>Add 300ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [400ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> to the pan with the <strong>chicken stock mix</strong></p><p>Reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1614618701169-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1614618701169-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1614618701169-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1614618701169-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1614618701169-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, rip the leaves off the <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and chop into small pieces</p><p>Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-1614618714271-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-1614618714271-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-1614618714271-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-1614618714271-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-1614618714271-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat and add a large knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced</strong> <strong>spring onion </strong>and <strong>spring greens </strong>with a splash of water<strong> </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until tender</p><p>Once the spring greens are tender, add the <strong>cooked potatoes</strong> and a large splash of <strong>milk</strong> to the pot</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and crush the potatoes gently with a potato masher – this is your <strong>crushed potato colcannon</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-1614618722245-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-1614618722245-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-1614618722245-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-1614618722245-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-1614618722245-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Roll the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1614618739131-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1614618739131-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1614618739131-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1614618739131-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1614618739131-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, transfer the chicken to a clean board and leave to rest for a couple of min before slicing</p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat and add the <strong>soft cheese</strong>, <strong>chopped basil </strong>(reserve a little for garnish!) and the<strong> juice</strong> from <strong>1/2</strong> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lemon</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>lemony basil sauce</strong></p><p>Slice the<strong> remaining lemon </strong>into wedges</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-1614618752420-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-1614618752420-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-1614618752420-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-1614618752420-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-1614618752420-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>crushed potato colcannon</strong> with the<strong> sliced chicken</strong> and<strong> lemony basil sauce</strong> to the side</p><p>Finish with a grind of<strong> black pepper</strong> and a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> remaining basil</strong></p><p>Bosh!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
